HEADWORD: Calaverite
<hw>Ca`la*ve"rite</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Min.)</fld>
<def>A bronze-yellow massive mineral with metallic luster; a telluride
of gold; -- first found in <etsep>Calaveras</etsep> County
California.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

